


Why consider investing in gold?









































Our Funds
What’s Driving Gold














Why consider investing in gold? 


Since the beginning of recorded history, gold has been treasured  for its scarcity and lasting value.
Investors look to gold as a store of value during times of economic uncertainty.
Gold demand is largely driven by traditional gift giving during cultural festivals, weddings and holidays in many parts of the world, especially India and China.
Gold acts as a portfolio diversifier, often moving differently than other assets.






I Want to Learn More


I Want to Open an Account















Gold mining stocks are a way for investors to gain exposure to gold. 










Our funds can provide this investment access:


Gold and Precious Metals Fund (USERX)
The Gold and Precious Metals Fund focuses on companies currently pulling gold or precious minerals from the ground. These “senior producers” generally have the largest market caps in the mining sector.








